<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="060" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Auth audit — verify FR-23 / NFR-08 / ADR-028 compliance across all new code</title>
    <phase>Phase F — Integration &amp; Verification</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020, 021, 022, 023, 024, 025, 026, 030, 031, 032, 033, 034, 035, 040, 041, 042, 043, 044, 045</dependencies>
    <blocks>070</blocks>
    <tags>auth, code-review, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Read-only audit producing a report. STANDARD rigor per task-execute decision tree — no production code changes unless violations are found (which open follow-up tasks). The audit itself is a verification gate, not a code implementation.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>F</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Read-only audit. Can run in parallel with other Phase F audits (061, 062, 063) — they touch independent verification surfaces.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Audit every file authored or modified by Phases B / C / D / E (tasks 020–045 and 050–051
    where applicable) for compliance with FR-23, NFR-08, and ADR-028 INV-1..INV-8. Three
    checks: (a) zero `accessToken` props or state snapshots anywhere in new code; (b) every
    BFF fetch uses `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth` — no direct `fetch(` calls
    against BFF URLs; (c) the function-based auth contract is honored — no references to
    retired patterns (`tokenBridge.ts`, `BridgeStrategy`). Produce a verification memo. If
    violations exist, open remediation tasks BEFORE Phase G begins.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior code reviewer specialized in Spaarke Auth v2 invariants (ADR-028 INV-1..INV-8).
    Comfortable with `git diff master..HEAD` enumeration, ripgrep audit patterns, and the
    authenticatedFetch / useAuth() function-based contract. Bias toward zero tolerance on
    token-snapshot anti-patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A verification memo at
    `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/audit-auth-2026-XX-XX.md` lists every
    new file in Phase B/C/D/E, the audit result per file (PASS / FAIL with line numbers),
    and a roll-up status (CLEAN / VIOLATIONS-FOUND). If VIOLATIONS-FOUND, follow-up
    remediation tasks are opened before Phase G is permitted to start. If CLEAN, the memo
    explicitly states "no violations; Phase G unblocked."
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      ADR-028 (Spaarke Auth v2) defines a function-based auth contract: `authenticatedFetch`
      and per-request `getAccessToken()` are the ONLY sanctioned BFF call paths. Token props
      and state snapshots are explicitly prohibited (INV-3, INV-4). Retired patterns
      `tokenBridge.ts` and `BridgeStrategy` are removed. This project added many React
      components across Phases B/C/D and possibly a BFF endpoint extension in Phase E;
      every one of them must follow the contract. This audit is the project-level gate
      before deployment.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/ (all Phase B/C/D files)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PaneHeader/ (Phase A)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs (Phase E, if executed)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">INV-3: no token props. INV-4: no state snapshots. INV-1..INV-2: per-request `getAccessToken()` via `authenticatedFetch`. INV-5..INV-8: no static auth state.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-23 — function-based auth contract across all new code. NFR-08 — zero token-snapshot patterns.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">This is a READ-ONLY audit. Do not edit production code in this task. If violations are found, open follow-up tasks and BLOCK Phase G until remediated.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Audit memo location: `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/audit-auth-2026-XX-XX.md` (date in filename = today, YYYY-MM-DD).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/bff-url-normalization.md</file>
      <file>.claude/AUDIT-FINDINGS-AUTH-SYSTEM.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/auth-deployment-setup.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Enumerate all new/modified files">
      Run `git diff --name-only master..HEAD` to enumerate every file added or modified on
      the project worktree branch. Filter to source files under `src/` — exclude `projects/`,
      `docs/`, `.claude/`, `notes/`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Grep for accessToken props/state">
      Across the enumerated files, grep for: `accessToken` (case-sensitive), `access_token`,
      `Authorization\s*:\s*['\"]Bearer`, `useState.*[Tt]oken`. Capture any hit with file +
      line number.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Grep for direct fetch() calls bypassing authenticatedFetch">
      Across the enumerated files, grep for `\bfetch\(` (excluding within `authenticatedFetch`
      implementation files in `@spaarke/auth` itself). Inspect each hit: if the target URL
      points at a BFF endpoint and `authenticatedFetch` is NOT in scope, flag as violation.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Grep for retired patterns">
      Across the enumerated files, grep for `tokenBridge`, `BridgeStrategy`, `TokenBridge`.
      Any hit is a violation (these patterns are retired per ADR-028).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Write audit memo">
      Create `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/audit-auth-{today}.md` with:
      <list>
        <item>Header: date, scope (Phases B/C/D/E), auditor (claude-code task 060)</item>
        <item>Files audited: full list from step 1</item>
        <item>Findings: per check (accessToken / direct fetch / retired patterns) with file + line + verdict</item>
        <item>Roll-up: CLEAN or VIOLATIONS-FOUND</item>
        <item>If VIOLATIONS-FOUND: list of follow-up remediation task IDs to open</item>
        <item>Gate decision: "Phase G unblocked" or "Phase G BLOCKED pending remediation tasks NNN"</item>
      </list>
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Open remediation tasks if needed">
      If violations are found, draft remediation task POMLs (one per violation cluster) and
      add them to TASK-INDEX.md. Phase G (tasks 070+) cannot begin until remediation tasks
      are COMPLETE.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Bash">`git diff --name-only master..HEAD`</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Audit for accessToken, direct fetch, retired patterns</tool>
    <tool name="Read">Inspect ambiguous matches in their file context</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Audit memo</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">TASK-INDEX.md (if opening remediation tasks)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/audit-auth-{today}.md</output>
    <output type="report">Task completion report with CLEAN or VIOLATIONS-FOUND verdict + Phase G gate status</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Audit memo exists at `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/audit-auth-{today}.md` and is dated.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Memo lists every file modified across Phases B/C/D/E (verified against `git diff --name-only master..HEAD`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Memo records the three audit checks (accessToken, direct fetch, retired patterns) per file with verdict.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Memo issues a single CLEAN or VIOLATIONS-FOUND roll-up verdict.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">If VIOLATIONS-FOUND: remediation tasks exist in TASK-INDEX.md and Phase G is documented as BLOCKED until they complete.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">If CLEAN: memo explicitly states "Phase G unblocked" — this is the gate that authorizes deployment task 070.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    This task MUST be executed via the `task-execute` skill from `.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md`.
  </execution>

  <notes>
    Completed 2026-05-20 by claude-code via task-execute (STANDARD rigor).

    Audit memo: `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/audit-auth-2026-05-20.md`

    Roll-up: CLEAN — 46 source files audited across Phases A/B/C/D/E (waves 0–4); zero violations.

    Checks performed:
    - (a) `accessToken` props/state: 11 hits, all in JSDoc/comments documenting ADR-028 compliance. PASS.
    - (a-2) `Authorization: Bearer` literals: 2 hits, both in `__tests__/*` mocking expected header. PASS.
    - (b) Retired patterns (tokenBridge, BridgeStrategy, XrmStrategy, __SPAARKE_BFF_TOKEN__, etc.): 0 hits. PASS.
    - (c) Raw `fetch(`: 4 hits (2 comments, 2 source). The 2 source hits in SprkChat.tsx lines 1098 + 1682 are legitimate D-AUTH-7 exceptions (SSE streaming with required `// Auth v2 (D-AUTH-7):` justification comment). `git blame` confirms both lines were authored by the predecessor auth-v2 project (commit 918b08307, 2026-05-19); no R3 commit modified them. PASS.
    - (d) `authenticatedFetch` adoption: confirmed at WelcomePanel, HistoryOverlay, WorkspaceHomeTab, ConversationPane, useDailyBriefing, SprkChat one-shot persist path. PASS.
    - (e) BFF endpoint filter chain (task 050): `.AddAiAuthorizationFilter().RequireRateLimiting("ai-stream")` preserved on `/sessions/{sessionId}/messages` and `/sessions/{sessionId}/refine` routes in ChatEndpoints.cs. PASS.

    Gate decision: Phase G UNBLOCKED. Task 070 (deploy SpaarkeAi production) and successors authorized to proceed.

    No remediation tasks opened.
  </notes>
</task>
